The paper focuses on automatic test generation for software programs, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of fuzzing to find bugs in programs suggests that the paper could also be classified under the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper specifically targets smart contracts, which are programs written in a programming language specific to blockchain technology, suggesting that it could also be classified under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of an online static analysis to guide the fuzzer suggests that the paper could also be classified under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the technique's effectiveness suggests that the paper could also be classified under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
